CASE 5: Microservices Architecture with CDN and Load Balancer doing URL Routing
================================================================================

Suppose ek microservices architecture hai jisme multiple services hain.

Har service ke multiple instances different servers par run kar rahe hain.

In services ke traffic ko route karne ke liye ek Load Balancer use ho raha hai
jo URL/path based routing support karta hai.

Is case me separate API Gateway mandatory nahi hai.

Load Balancer khud URL based routing kar sakta hai.

Example:

    /users/**     -> User Service instances
    /orders/**    -> Order Service instances
    /payments/**  -> Payment Service instances

Is setup me CDN bhi present hai.

Flow:

    User
      |
      v
    DNS
      |
      | returns CDN IP
      v
    Nearby CDN Edge
      |
      | cache miss
      v
    Load Balancer with URL Routing
      |
      |----------------------|----------------------|
      v                      v                      v
    User Service          Order Service          Payment Service
    Instances             Instances              Instances

Explanation:

    Yahan API Gateway nahi hai.
    Load Balancer hi path based routing kar raha hai.

    Modern Load Balancers, jaise AWS ALB, path based routing support karte hain.

    But API Gateway ke advanced features jaise rate limiting, API keys,
    request transformation, etc. Load Balancer me limited ho sakte hain.

================================================================================
CASE 6: Monolithic Architecture with CDN and Load Balancer
================================================================================

Suppose ek monolithic application hai.

Uske multiple instances different servers par run kar rahe hain.
In instances ke traffic ko distribute karne ke liye ek Load Balancer hai.

CDN bhi present hai.

Is case me DNS resolution ke baad CDN ka IP return hota hai.

Flow:

    User
      |
      v
    DNS
      |
      | returns CDN IP
      v
    Nearby CDN Edge
      |
      | cache miss
      v
    Load Balancer
      |
      |------------------|------------------|
      v                  v                  v
    Monolith App 1     Monolith App 2     Monolith App 3

Explanation:

    Load Balancer ka kaam sirf monolithic application ke multiple instances ke beech
    traffic distribute karna hai.

    URL routing application ke andar hoti hai.

Example in Spring Boot:

    /users      -> UserController
    /orders     -> OrderController
    /payments   -> PaymentController

    Ye sab same Spring Boot application ke andar handle hote hain.
